1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,611
And it didn't take a brilliant man or a wealthy man or a lucky man.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:11,571
All, and I hesitate to use the word all because all means so much sometimes,

3
00:00:11,840 --> 00:00:17,090
all it took was a persistent man who never thought he was defeated.

4
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:23,170
Behind this prosperous and respected company is the story of a man fighting,

5
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:28,931
battling his way upward, losing ten years' savings in his first six months in business,

6
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:34,211
living in his office several months because he lacked money to pay rent on an apartment,

7
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:40,691
turning down numerous good jobs because he wanted more to stay with his idea and make it work,

8
00:00:40,961 --> 00:00:46,610
hearing prospects for his service say no a hundred times as often as they said yes,

9
00:00:47,761 --> 00:00:55,170
During the seven unbelievably hard years it took him to succeed, I never heard my friend complain once.

10
00:00:55,441 --> 00:00:58,451
He'd explain, Dave, I'm learning.

11
00:00:58,641 --> 00:01:03,251
This is competitive business, and because it's intangible, it's hard to sell.

12
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:04,850
But I'm learning how.

13
00:01:05,201 --> 00:01:06,530
And he did.

14
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:12,290
Once I told my friend that this experience must be taking a lot out of him,

15
00:01:12,321 --> 00:01:19,090
but he replied, no, it's not taking something out of me, it's putting something into me instead.

16
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:30,610
Check the lives of the people in Who's Who in America, and you'll find that those who have succeeded in a major way have been pounded by losing situations.

17
00:01:30,961 --> 00:01:40,131
Each person in this elite corps of successful men has encountered opposition, discouragement, setbacks, personal misfortune.

18
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:50,850
Read the biographies and autobiographies of great people, and again you discover that each of these people could have surrendered to setbacks many times.

19
00:01:51,441 --> 00:01:52,530
Or do this.

20
00:01:52,961 --> 00:01:57,651
Learn the background of the president of your company or the mayor of your city,

21
00:01:57,761 --> 00:02:01,251
or select any person you consider a real success.

22
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:07,730
When you probe, you'll discover the individual has overcome big, real obstacles.

23
00:02:08,641 --> 00:02:15,090
It is not possible to win high-level success without meeting opposition, hardship, and setback.

24
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:19,730
But it is possible to use setbacks to propel you forward.

25
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:21,331
Let's see how.

26
00:02:22,641 --> 00:02:31,170
I saw some commercial airline statistics recently showing that there is only one fatality per 10 billion miles flown.

27
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:35,571
Air travel is a magnificently safe way to go these days.

28
00:02:35,761 --> 00:02:39,090
Unfortunately, air accidents still occur.

29
00:02:39,201 --> 00:02:46,530
But when they do, the Civil Aviation Administration is on the scene quickly to find out what caused the crash.

30
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:51,090
Fragments of metal are picked up from miles around and pieced together.

31
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:55,251
A variety of experts reconstruct what probably happened.

32
00:02:55,521 --> 00:02:58,211
Witnesses and survivors are interviewed.

33
00:02:58,401 --> 00:03:05,811
The investigation goes on for weeks, months, until the question, what caused this crash, is answered.

34
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:13,970
Once the CAA has the answer, immediate steps are taken to prevent a similar accident from happening again.

35
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:21,170
If the crash was caused by a structural defect, other planes of that type must have that defect corrected.

36
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:26,290
Or if certain instruments are found faulty, corrections must be made.

37
00:03:27,441 --> 00:03:34,451
Literally hundreds of safety devices on modern aircraft have resulted from CAA investigations.

38
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:42,850
The CAA studies setbacks to pave the way to safer air travel, and it's obvious that their efforts pay off.
